netstat
    netstat -a : Listing all ports (both TCP and UDP) using netstat -a option.
    -at: Listing only TCP (Transmission Control Protocol) port connections using netstat -at.
    -au: Listing only UDP (User Datagram Protocol ) port connections using netstat -au.
    -l: Listing all active listening ports connections with netstat -l.
    -lt: Listing all active listening TCP ports by using option netstat -lt.
    -lu: Listing all active listening UDP ports by using option netstat -lu.
    -lx: Listing all active UNIX listening ports using netstat -lx.
    -s: Displays statistics by protocol. By default, statistics are shown for the TCP, UDP, ICMP, and IP protocols. The -s parameter can be used to specify a set of protocols.
    -st: Showing statistics of only TCP protocol by using option netstat -st

    reference
        https://www.tecmint.com/20-netstat-commands-for-linux-network-management/#targetText=netstat%20(network%20statistics)%20is%20a,on%20Windows%20OS%20as%20well.